Cynthia Rogers Stone, a third-year law student at the Suffolk University School of Law in Boston, and John Joseph Phelan, a pension trust officer at the Bank of New England/Essex in Peabody, Mass., were married yesterday at the Wellesley (Mass.) Congregational Church. The Rev. William B. Abernethy performed the ceremony. Mrs. Phelan, a graduate of Connecticut College, is a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Wadsworth S. Stone of Wellesley Hills, Mass. Mr. Phelan, a graduate of Fordham University who earned an M.B.A. from Boston College, is the son of Mr. and Mrs. Joseph F. Phelan of Southbury, Conn.
